estricted byways that are not open to all traffic</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Although we have not collected evidence regarding this issue we do have anecdotal evidence of disturbance to nesting birds caused by use of UUCRs that cross nature reserves in the </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Breckland</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> area of Norfolk. This relates to UUCRs that cross East </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Wretham</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> Heath and </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Weeting</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> Heath, which are both part of </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Breckland</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> Special Protection Area (SPA), which is designated for stone curlew. Nesting density of Stone curlew have been shown to decrease in the proximity of both new development and by roads according and </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Breckland</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> Council has adopted polices with strict guidelines relating to development within 1500m of nests that are on the SPA.   A change of use from UUCR to restricted byway would lessen disturbance to this European protected species.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">John </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Hiskett</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">CEnv</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> MCIEEM</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Senior Conservation Officer</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">9 September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>